{
  "retailer": "targetsports",
  "retailer_slug": "target-sports",
  "platform": "generic-sitemap",
  "base": "https://www.targetsportsusa.com",
  "comment": "Caliber-paths config (expansion #4, Step 2). Version-controlled replacement for the inline CALIBER_PATHS dict in scraper_targetsports.py. Source of truth for which category URLs the scraper fetches; the URLs themselves are NOT derivable from calibers.json (that is why this is a separate file, not a *_gen.* artifact). Loaded at runtime by scraper_lib.load_caliber_paths('targetsports'), which returns ONLY status=='active' entries. Each caliber maps to a LIST of entries because one of our combined calibers can split into several upstream category pages (.223 Rem + 5.56 NATO; .308 Win + 7.62x51 NATO) — the TSUSA multi-URL lesson. No URL is added here without passing the validation harness (Step 3): 200, no redirect, page title names the caliber, product titles pass the caliber gate at a high rate. status: active = fetched; candidate = discovered, validated, awaiting sign-off (never fetched); parked = known-bad/walled (never fetched). expect_landed is the redirect-guard / validation target (the path the request must land on). query is the sort/paging suffix, stored apart from path so the redirect guard can ignore it. title_filter is an optional regex for mixed-caliber category pages (null here; TSUSA pages are single-caliber). validation/source/approved_* are provenance.",
